    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>sliced spring greens</strong> to a large piece of <strong>tin foil </strong>(or two!) with <strong>half </strong>the <strong>sliced chilli </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>sliced garlic </strong>and a generous splash of <strong>cold water</strong> and a knob of <strong>butter</strong></p><p>Scrunch the foil around the spring greens to form a tightly sealed parcel[s] and add to a baking tray</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 10-12 min or until the spring greens are tender – this is your<strong> greens</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
