    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a pot with a knob of <strong>butter </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once melted, add your <strong>jerk paste</strong>, 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp] </span><strong>flour </strong>and cook for 30 secs, stirring frequently, until you're left with a sandy paste</p><p>Whisk in the <strong>stock</strong>, then bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 4-5 min or until thickened – this is your <strong>jerk-spiced gravy</strong></p>",
